songs.title: Chelsea Hotel
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1: Lana Del Rey]
I remember you well
At the Chelsea Hotel
You were talking so brave and so sweet
Giving me head on the unmade bed
While the limousines waiting on streets
But those were the reasons and that was New York
We were living for the money and the flash
That was called love for the workers in song
Probably still is for those of them left

[Chorus: Lana Del Rey & Adam Cohen]
But you've got a way
Didn't you babe?
You just turned on your back on the crowd
You've got the way
And the answers to say
"I need you, I don't need you
I need you, I don't need you
I need you, I don't need you
And all that driving around

[Verse 2: Adam Cohen]
I remember you well
At the Chelsea Hotel
You were famous, the part of the legend
You told me again, you prefer handsome men
But for me you would make an exception

[Bridge: Adam Cohen & Lana Del Rey]
And clenching your fist
For the ones like us
You fixed yourself
You said, "Well, never mind
YWe are ugly, but we have the music

[Chorus: Lana Del Rey & Adam Cohen]
But you've got a way
Didn't you babe?
You just turned on your back on the crowd
You've got the way
And the answers to say
"I need you, I don't need you
I need you, I don't need you
I need you, I don't need you
I need you, I don't need you
I need you, I don't need you
Said I need you, I don't need you
Said I need you, I don't need you
And all that driving around

[Outro: Lana Del Rey , Adam Cohen]
Yeah, yeah, yeah
I don't mean to suggest
That I loved you the best
I can keep track of each fallen robin
I I remember you well
At the Chelsea Hotel
That's all, I don't even think of you that often
